<paragraph id="156F570EFFF6FF88B1FD5387FD38F97C" blockId="121.[151,1437,1509,1787]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFF6FF88B1FD5387FE27FA30" bold="true" box="[151,395,1509,1535]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Principal characters</emphasis>
: Body of adult female oval to elongate oval. Antennae normally each with 7 segments, Legs well developed but small for size of body; hind coxa surrounded by minute pores on adjacent derm; claw without a denticle. A single pair of cerarii present, on anal lobes. Multilocular disc pores present on dorsum at least on abdomen, also present on venter of abdomen, thorax, and around margins forward to head. Trilocular pores present. Circulus, if present, often ‘hourglass’ shaped. Anterior and posterior ostioles present. Oral collar tubular ducts present on venter (
<bibRefCitation id="71412AFFFFF6FF88B00C50FBFD2BF97C" author="Williams, D. J. &amp; Watson, G. W." box="[358,647,1689,1715]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" refId="ref98131" refString="Williams, D. J. &amp; Watson, G. W. (1988) The Scale Insects of the Tropical South Pacific Region. Pt. 2: The Mealybugs (Pseudococcidae). CAB International, Wallingford, 260 pp." type="book" year="1988">Williams &amp; Watson 1988</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="156F570EFFF6FF88B1AD50DFFDC5F934" blockId="121.[151,1437,1509,1787]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFF6FF88B1AD50DFFEE4F918" bold="true" box="[199,328,1725,1751]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Comments</emphasis>
: Worldwide, three species are included in 
<taxonomicName id="D2D02C8DFFF6FF88B27450DFFABEF917" authority="(Garcia Morales et al. 2016)" baseAuthorityName="Garcia Morales" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[798,1298,1725,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Saccharicoccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFF6FF88B27450DFFC62F918" box="[798,974,1725,1751]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Saccharicoccus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="71412AFFFFF6FF88B2B650DFFAA7F917" author="Garcia Morales M. &amp; Denno, B. D. &amp; Miller, D. R. &amp; Miller, G. L. &amp; Ben-Dov, Y. &amp; Hardy, N. B." box="[988,1291,1725,1752]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" refId="ref89637" refString="Garcia Morales M., Denno, B. D., Miller, D. R., Miller, G. L., Ben-Dov, Y. &amp; Hardy, N. B. (2016) ScaleNet: a literature-based model of scale insect biology and systematics. Database. Available from: http: // scalenet. info (accessed 30 January 2021) https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / database / bav 118" type="url" year="2016">
García Morales 
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFF6FF88B5FA50DCFB6DF918" box="[1168,1217,1725,1751]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; one species is known from 
<collectingCountry id="6DC7179EFFF6FF88B0285083FEC3F934" box="[322,367,1761,1787]" name="Iran" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="71412AFFFFF6FF88B0175083FDF1F934" author="Moghaddam, M." box="[381,605,1761,1787]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref94836" refString="Moghaddam, M. (2013 a) A review of the mealybugs (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Pseudococcidae, Putoidae and Rhizoecidae) of Iran, with descriptions of four new species and three new records for the Iranian fauna. Zootaxa, 3632 (1), 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3632.1.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Moghaddam 2013a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
